data.enText: to press or squeeze sth together or into a smaller space; to be pressed or squeezed in this way

data.chText: 她的双唇抿成了一道缝。
data.enText: Her lips compressed into a thin line.
to reduce sth and fit it into a smaller space or amount of time

data.chText: 主要的论证被压缩进了一个章节。
data.enText: The main arguments were compressed into one chapter.
to make computer files, etc. smaller so that they use less space on a disk, etc.
a cloth that is pressed onto a part of the body to stop the loss of blood, reduce pain, etc.

simple_means.memory_skill: com 表加强 + press 压 → 一再压 → 压缩

ex.chText: 他踩下油门，但是汽车没有动。
ex.enText: He pressed the gas pedal, but the car didn't move.

ex.chText: 窗子上都是灰，别把脸贴在上面！
ex.enText: Don't press your face against the dusty window!

synonyms.bx: 指某个人或物体在某一表面上施压。

ex.chText: 这种材料便于压缩，张开时速度又快。
ex.enText: This material compresses well and then expands rapidly.

ex.chText: 山坡上的积雪被压成了冰。
ex.enText: Snow falling on the mountainsides is compressed into ice.

synonyms.bx: 指外部因素使某物体积变小。

ex.chText: 即使在冬天她也不会戴帽子，她怕头发被帽子压瘪了。
ex.enText: She won't wear a hat even in winter in case her hair is squashed down by it.

ex.chText: 公交车上人很多，所以蛋糕受了些挤压。
ex.enText: There were too many people on the bus and so the cake got a bit squashed.

synonyms.bx: 指将某物压扁，常含压碎或压坏之意。

ex.chText: 没看到信号之前不要扣动扳机。
ex.enText: Don't squeeze the trigger until you see the signal.

ex.chText: 她捏捏他的手，然后离开了。
ex.enText: She squeezed his hand and left.

ex.chText: 往肉丸子上挤点橙子汁。
ex.enText: Squeeze a bit of orange juice onto the meatballs.

synonyms.bx: 指用手或手指用力捏紧某物，也指挤出液体。

tr: a cloth pad or dressing (with or without medication) applied firmly to some part of the body (to relieve discomfort or reduce fever)
make more compact by or as if by pressing

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /kəm'pres/. The noun is pronounced /'kɒmpres/. 动词读作 /kəm'pres/，名词读作 /'kɒmpres/。

value.def: When you compress something or when it compresses, it is pressed or squeezed so that it takes up less space.

example.ex: Poor posture, sitting or walking slouched over, compresses the body's organs...
example.tran: 坐着或者走路的时候低头垂肩，这种不正确的姿势会压迫体内的器官。

example.ex: Air will compress but the brake fluid won't.
example.tran: 空气会压缩，但是刹车油不会。

example.ex: The compression of the wood is easily achieved.

value.def: If you compress something such as a piece of writing or a description, you make it shorter.

example.ex: He never understood how to organize or compress large masses of material...
example.tran: 他从来就不懂如何对大篇的材料进行整理或精简。

example.ex: All those three books are compacted and compressed into one book.
example.tran: 那三本书的内容全都压缩进一本书了。

value.def: If an event is compressed into a short space of time, it is given less time to happen than normal or previously.

example.ex: The four debates will be compressed into an unprecedentedly short eight-day period...
example.tran: 这4场辩论将被压缩到短短8天的时间，这是前所未有的。

example.ex: Some courses such as engineering had to be compressed.
example.tran: 有些课程，比如工程学，必须减少课时。

value.def: A compress is a pad of wet or dry cloth pressed on part of a patient's body to reduce fever.

example.ex: Sore throats may be relieved by cold compresses.
example.tran: 喉咙痛用冷敷布敷一下可能会好一些。
